The paper deals with finding optimal strategies for a game, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The authors use linear programming and linear extension techniques, which are common in the fields of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the implementation and observation of the algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
